events.name: TensorFlow Dev Summit 2018 Extended Gusau
events.description:
TensorFlow Dev Summit brings together a diverse mix of machine learning users from around the world for a full day of highly technical talks and demos. TensorFlow Dev Summit Extended Gusau aims to achieve that by bringing researchers and developers who are already in machine learning field up to speed with what TensorFlow is, the advances made in TensorFlow library and how to deploy them in their projects.
Our expert speaker from Edge Analytica will show us examples on how to run simple linear regression model and image recognition using the TensorFlow libraries.
But before that, we're going to entertain you with recorded video of TensorFlow Dev Summit 2018.

*** Come with your laptop ***

Agenda:
4:00PM ---> Registration & checking in
4:30PM ---> Showing of recorded TensorFlow Dev Summit 2018
6:30PM ---> Break
7:00PM ---> Codelab session
9:00PM ---> Event end

events.name: Flutter Study Jam

venue.name: Hafsat Hall, Ten o Seven Restaurant

events.description:
Flutter is Google’s mobile app SDK for crafting high-quality native interfaces on iOS and Android in record time. Flutter works with existing code, is used by developers and organizations around the world, and is free and open source.

Want to get started with mobile app development? You are at the right place at the right time.

Together we'll walk you through a seven hour tutorial in two weeks (i.e. on 27th Oct. and 10th Nov., 2018) on Flutter Udacity Course prepared by Google instructors. You will be able to get hands-on experience with Flutter and build a Flutter app while learning the fundamentals.

Click the link below for more information on Flutter
https://flutter.io/get-started/install/
https://youtu.be/OlqeHypxJqA

***The BIGGEST BONUS OF ALL!***
Everyone, who completes the course will get a Google-offered Study Jam completion certificate and a profile badge.
And as always refreshment is on the table!

GDG DevFest 2018 is our annual all-day developer conference that offers speaker sessions across multiple product areas, codelabs, hackathon and more!
In this session, we are going to introduce Google ARCore. ARCore is Google’s platform for building augmented reality experiences. Using different APIs, ARCore enables your phone to sense its environment, understand the world and interact with information. Some of the APIs are available across Android and iOS to enable shared AR experiences.

events.name: Cloud Study Jam Gusau

venue.name: Hafsat Hall, Ten o Seven Restaurant

events.description:
Want to get started on the Google Cloud, but don't know where to begin? Join us for our Cloud Study Jam!
Get official Google training, a $55+ value, free of charge. Together we'll work through several Google Cloud labs. You will get hands-on experience with the Cloud Console, Kubernetes, Security, IoT on Cloud, and Machine Learning.
Then after our live session, you will have free access to more labs you can finish at home. Complete all labs in the quest and earn a Google-hosted badge for your online profile, and additional 30 days access to the training platform to compete any labs you want.

Bring a laptop and charger (PC, Mac or Chromebook)! The labs will run on all of the latest versions of the popular browsers. For the best experience, make sure your laptop has Firefox or Chrome installed. Don’t forget your charger.

10:00 am ---------Welcome!
10:05 am ---------Get free access to Qwiklabs
10:10 am --------- Lab 1: Introduction to GCP
10:45 am --------- Lab 2: Introduction to Cloud SQL
11:10 am --------- Lab 3: CloudML Engine Qwik Start
11:30 am --------- Break
12:00 pm ---------Cloud Speech API
1:00 pm ---------- Event ends - THANK YOU!
